    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-07T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-07T07:00:00-05:00" n="830"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d830">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/1055: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-07T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 7, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 7—10:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>701. Embassy’s 697, December 6, 4 p.m. Woermann has just called me on the
                    telephone and informed me that the Brussels meeting had been postponed for a
                    week. He said that this postponement was solely because of the illness of the
                    German who would attend.</p>
                <p>In relation to my telegram under reference Woermann is at present Acting Foreign
                    Minister. Repeated to London for Rublee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
